20/08/2006
OHRID, Macedonia -- US Ambassador to Skopje Gillian Milovanovic said on Friday (18 August) that she expects Macedonia to be invited to join NATO in 2008.
Visiting Ohrid to mark the 5th anniversary of the Peace Agreement, Milovanovic said she anticipates progress in reforms and NATO integration.
She stressed, however, that the various political parties must assume responsibility and work together to boost the economy, fight corruption and strengthen interethnic relations.
(Dnevnik - 19/08/06;
MRT - 18/08/06)
